  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "Double Talk",
    "overview_subtitle": "Solving One-Step Addition Equations",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students use double number lines to solve one-step addition equations of the form <math><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>, where <math><mi>p</mi></math> and <math><mi>q</mi></math> are whole numbers. They connect the structure of this model to inverse operations and solve one-step addition equations. Students then practice solving one-step addition equations with non-negative rational numbers."
  },
